## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of sources and the inherent biases present in opinion-based articles. The ethicality of eating meat is a subjective topic, and perspectives can vary widely based on cultural, personal, and philosophical beliefs. Additionally, the environmental data presented may not account for all variables, such as regional differences in agricultural practices. Further research, including empirical studies and cross-cultural analyses, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.